The relative quantum yield (
                           Φ
                        ) of the carbon dots was measured using a fluorescence spectrometer excited at 340 nm A carbon dot solution in DI water (n = 1.33) and a solution of quinine sulfate in 0.1 M sulfuric acid as reference (n = 1.33, quantum yield of 54% at 360 nm) were prepared. The quantum yield (
                           Φ
                        ) was calculated based on a previous report [27].
